declarations.comments:

declarations.comments:
- succ: `succ bottom >>= succ >>= succ ... succ [cardinality - 1 times] = top`
- pred: `pred top    >>= pred >>= pred ... pred [cardinality - 1 times] = bottom`
- predsucc: `forall a > bottom: pred a >>= succ = Just a`
- succpred: `forall a < top:  succ a >>= pred = Just a`
- enumpred: `forall a > bottom: fromEnum <$> pred a = Just (fromEnum a - 1)`
- enumsucc: `forall a < top:  fromEnum <$> succ a = Just (fromEnum a + 1)`
- compare: `compare e1 e2 = compare (fromEnum e1) (fromEnum e2)`
- tofromenum: toEnum (fromEnum a) = Just a
declarations.title: checkBoundedEnum

declarations.comments:
- Reflexivity: `x == x = true`
- Symmetry: `x == y = y == x`
- Transitivity: if `x == y` and `y == z` then `x == z`
- Negation: `x /= y = not (x == y)`
declarations.title: checkEq

declarations.comments:
- Integral domain: `a /= 0` and `b /= 0` implies `a * b /= 0`
- Multiplicative Euclidean function: ``a = (a / b) * b + (a `mod` b)``
  where `degree a > 0` and `degree a <= degree (a * b)`
declarations.title: checkEuclideanRing

declarations.comments: - Non-zero multiplicative inverse: ``a `mod` b = 0` for all `a` and `b`
declarations.title: checkField

declarations.comments:
- Associativity:
  - `a || (b || c) = (a || b) || c`
  - `a && (b && c) = (a && b) && c`
- Commutativity:
  - `a || b = b || a`
  - `a && b = b && a`
- Absorption:
  - `a || (a && b) = a`
  - `a && (a || b) = a`
- Idempotent:
  - `a || a = a`
  - `a && a = a`
- Identity:
  - `a || ff = a`
  - `a && tt = a`
- Implication:
  - ``a `implies` a = tt``
  - ``a && (a `implies` b) = a && b``
  - ``b && (a `implies` b) = b``
  - ``a `implies` (b && c) = (a `implies` b) && (a `implies` c)``
- Complemented:
  - ``not a = a `implies` ff``
declarations.title: checkHeytingAlgebra

declarations.comments:
- Left identity: `mempty <> x = x`
- Right identity: `x <> mempty = x`
declarations.title: checkMonoid

declarations.comments:
- Reflexivity: `a <= a`
- Antisymmetry: if `a <= b` and `b <= a` then `a = b`
- Transitivity: if `a <= b` and `b <= c` then `a <= c`
declarations.title: checkOrd

declarations.comments: - Additive inverse: `a - a = a + (-a) = (-a) + a = zero`
declarations.title: checkRing

declarations.comments: - Associativity: `(x <> y) <> z = x <> (y <> z)`
declarations.title: checkSemigroup

declarations.comments:
- Commutative monoid under addition:
  - Associativity: `(a + b) + c = a + (b + c)`
  - Identity: `zero + a = a + zero = a`
  - Commutative: `a + b = b + a`
- Monoid under multiplication:
  - Associativity: `(a * b) * c = a * (b * c)`
  - Identity: `one * a = a * one = a`
- Multiplication distributes over addition:
  - Left distributivity: `a * (b + c) = (a * b) + (a * c)`
  - Right distributivity: `(a + b) * c = (a * c) + (b * c)`
- Annihiliation: `zero * a = a * zero = zero`
declarations.title: checkSemiring
